skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Significant height of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Average height of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Density of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Precipitation duration (liquid water equivalent) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind stress on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Phytoplankton Colour Index
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Maximum height of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The maximum vertical distance between a wave crest and the immediately preceding or following through during a specified observation period.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Average crest period of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Average zero crossing period of the highest 1/3rd of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The average period of the highest 1/3 of waves measured during a recording burst
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Direction of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Directional spreading of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Period of swell waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Mole fraction of carbon dioxide (dry air) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The proportion as a ratio of quantity of matter of CO2 in a sample of atmosphere expressed on a dry air basis
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Partial pressure of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The partial pressure of carbon dioxide in air
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Fugacity of carbon dioxide (at 100% humidity) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The fugacity (effective partial pressure allowing for non-ideal gas) of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere assuming a humidity of 100 per cent.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Mole fraction of carbon dioxide (dry air) in the equilibrated marine sample
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The proportion as a ratio of quantity of matter of CO2 in a sample of air equilibrated with seawater expressed on a dry air basis
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Electrical conductivity of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Current direction in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The direction towards which Eulerian current in the water column is flowing.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Horizontal visibility in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Pressure (measured variable) exerted by the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Measurement as a phenomenon (as opposed to a co-ordinate) of the force per unit area exerted by the atmosphere determined in-situ at a known altitude.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Root mean square height of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Acceptable proportion of signal returns
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Pings received as a percentage of pings sent
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Pressure (measured variable) exerted by the atmosphere and correction to sea level
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Measurement as a phenomenon (as opposed to a co-ordinate) of the force per unit area exerted by the atmosphere determined in-situ at a known altitude and converted to the value at sea level assuming an isothermal layer.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Temperature of the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The degree of hotness of the atmosphere expressed against a standard scale. Includes both IPTS-68 and ITS-90 scales.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Dew point temperature of the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The temperature to which air must cool to become saturated with water vapour
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Eastward current velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Speed of Eulerian current flow towards due east.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Eastward wind velocity in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The component of the wind blowing towards true east. The value could result from any kind of measurement or prediction.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Saturation of oxygen {O2} in the water body [dissolved phase]
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of chlorophyll per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The mass of all types of chlorophyll per unit volume of the water column held in particles of any size
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Northward current velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Speed of Eulerian current flow towards true north
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Northward wind velocity in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The component of the wind blowing towards true north. The value could result from any kind of measurement or prediction.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Precipitation rate (liquid water equivalent) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Relative humidity of the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The ratio of the amount of water vapour in the air compared to the maximum amount of water vapour that can theoretically be held at the air's temperature
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Practical salinity of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The quantity of dissolved ions (predominantly salt in seawater) expressed on a scale (PSS-78) based on the conductivity ratio of a seawater sample to a standard KCl solution.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Skin temperature of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Skin temperature of the water body measure by Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR)
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Temperature of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The degree of hotness of the water column expressed against a standard scale. Includes both IPTS-68 and ITS-90 scales.
skos:Concept.dc:source: (P011) BODC Parameter Usage Vocabulary

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Average height of the highest 1/10th of waves on the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Height of left Bragg peak in power spectrum
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Upward current velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Partial pressure of carbon dioxide in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The partial pressure of carbon dioxide in air in equilibrium with a water sample
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Height of right Bragg peak in power spectrum
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Current velocity error in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Power spectrum signal to noise ratio
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of chlorophyll per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The mass of all types of chlorophyll per unit mass of the water column held in particles of any size
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of oxygen {O2} per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of dissolved oxygen per unit volume of the water column. Oxygen may be expressed in terms of mass, volume or quantity of substance.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of oxygen {O2} per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of dissolved oxygen per unit mass of the water column. Oxygen may be expressed in terms of mass, volume or quantity of substance.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of nitrate {NO3} per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of nitrate per unit volume of the water column. Nitrate may be expressed in terms of mass or quantity of substance.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of nitrate {NO3} per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration (moles or mass) of nitrogen as nitrate per unit mass of the water column
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of silicate {SiO4} per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of silicate per unit volume of the water column. Silicate may be expressed in terms of mass or quantity of substance.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of ammonium {NH4} per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of ammonium per unit volume of the water column. Ammonium may be expressed in terms of mass or quantity of substance.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of silicate {SiO4} per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration (moles or mass) of silicon as silicate per unit mass of the water column
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of phosphate {PO4} per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of phosphate per unit volume of the water column. Phosphate may be expressed in terms of mass or quantity of substance
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Concentration of phosphate {PO4} per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration of phosphate dissolved per unit mass of the water column. Solute may be expressed in terms of mass, volume or quantity of substance
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Current speed in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The speed of Eulerian flow in the water column
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Specific humidity of the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Sound velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The rate at which sound travels through the water column
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Thickness of precipitation amount (liquid water equivalent) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Turbidity of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Estimate of suspended sediment concentration based on the proportion of a light transmission in the water column that is reflected back to a co-located receiver.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wet bulb temperature of the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind from direction in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Direction relative to true north from which the wind is blowing
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind speed in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Sustained speed of the wind (distance moved per unit time by a parcel of air) parallel to the ground at a given place and time
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind speed of gust in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Maximum speed of the wind (distance moved per unit time by a parcel of air) parallel to the ground during a gust event (generally regarded as an increase over sustained speed of more than 5m/s lasting less than 20 seconds).
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind to direction in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Present weather in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Visual observation using WMO code table 4677 or 4501
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Total alkalinity per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Concentration (moles or mass) of acid-neutralising bases per unit mass of the water column
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Acoustic signal return amplitude from the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Fugacity of carbon dioxide (at 100% humidity) in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Fugacity (partial pressure corrected for non-ideality of gases) of carbon dioxide in air that is in equilibrium with a seawater sample
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Fugacity anomaly (water - air) of carbon dioxide in the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The difference in the CO2 fugacity (effective partial pressure allowing for non-ideal gas) between air in equilibrium with seawater and the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: concentration of echinenone per unit mass of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The amount (mass or moles) of the specified pigment determined by HPLC assay of a sample collected by dissolution in acteone of the residue collected by GF/F filtration of a known volume of any water body. The quoted value either results from a single determination or the average of replicate determinations
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Abundance of biota
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The relative representation of flora and fauna in a particular sample or region.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Biotic taxonomic identification
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The identification of the biotic elements to the relevant scientific classification group (taxa), e.g. genus or species.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Pressure (measured variable) in the water body exerted by overlying sea water only
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The force per unit area exerted by the overlying sea water on a sensor located in the water column. Excludes the pressure due to sea ice, air and any other medium that may be present.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Downwelling vector irradiance as energy (longwave) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Downwelling vector irradiance as energy (solar (300-3000nm) wavelengths) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Pressure (measured variable) in the water body exerted by overlying sea water and any medium above it
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The force per unit area exerted by the overlying sea water, sea ice, air and any other medium that may be present on a sensor located in the water column.
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Temperature of oxygen determination
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Temperature for the equilibrated marine sample
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Pressure for the equilibrated marine sample
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Dry weight biomass per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wet weight biomass per unit volume of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Downwelling vector irradiance as photons (PAR wavelengths) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Downwelling vector irradiance as photons (PAR wavelengths) in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind speed (relative to moving platform) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Wind direction (relative to moving platform) in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Temperature anomaly of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Practical salinity anomaly of the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Detection of acoustic tag
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Sound recorded in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Fluorescence of the water body
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The amount of radiation generated in the water column in response to higher energy radiation transmission expressed relative to an unspecified baseline
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Water-leaving radiance from the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Colored Dissolved Organic Matter
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The amount of colored organic compounds (sometimes called yellow substance or gelbstoff) dissolved in a specified amount of water from any body of fresh or salt water
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Ocean heat content
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Hail duration in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Thickness of hail amount in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Hail intensity in the atmosphere
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Eastward geostrophic current velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Northward geostrophic current velocity in the water body
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Water-leaving radiance from the water body corrected for viewing angle dependance
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Normalised water-leaving radiance from the water body determined from Lw
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Normalised water-leaving radiance from the water body determined from Lw_Q
skos:Concept.dc:source: Australian Ocean Data Network parameter register
